= La izquierda de charola

It launches with a budget no honest party has: a "new force of the socialist left," lavishly postered, granted its registro with a speed the Comisión has never once shown you, its leaders young, telegenic, and formerly yours — two of them are faces from your own congress photographs, wearing new suits and the smiles of men whose rent is no longer a variable.

The design is stamped on every choice: its program is your program with the teeth pulled; its candidacies bloom precisely in your best districts; its posters answer questions no one asked about you in particular. Gobernación has concluded, the fuente confirms, that the cheapest way to contain a real left is to manufacture an affordable one — and let the two of you divide the same discontent.

- @contrastar: Fight it on substance: the record, the prisoners, the strikes — make authenticity the issue in every district it contests.
- @infiltrar_oficial: Put people inside it. A party built of the bought can be bought back — or at least read like a subscription.
- @desdenar: Ignore it. Manufactured parties are the regime's money set on fire; save your powder for the regime.

@contrastar
go-to: post_event
choose-if: political_capital >= 4
unavailable-subtitle: Contrast requires a platform loud enough to draw the comparison — capital you lack this season.
on-arrival: political_capital -= 4; sup_students += 3; sup_colonos += 2; fe_voto += 1; expediente += 2

The counter-campaign never names them, which is the art of it: a poster series on the Party's dead, a pamphlet reprinting your 1968 positions beside theirs (they had none; they did not exist), Benita's generation telling plaza audiences what the word militante cost before it paid. In district after district the manufactured party discovers the one deficit money cannot cover: it has no funerals to point to. The discount left keeps its budget. You keep the base.

@infiltrar_oficial
go-to: post_event
choose-if: organizers >= 3 and inteligencia >= 15
unavailable-subtitle: Infiltration is skilled labor: it takes spare cadres and the craft to keep them unread.
on-arrival: inteligencia += 4; political_capital += 1; expediente += 3; unity -= 1

Three of yours join the new party with convincing resentment and rise, as talent rises in a house built of the bought, immediately. Within a year you read its candidate lists before its own executive does, know which Gobernación desk feeds it, and can nudge its district choices away from your strongholds — a competitor whose steering wheel you can, on good months, lean on. The ortodoxos are told nothing, on the principle that some meals should not be described at the table.

@desdenar
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: unity += 1; funds += 1

The analysis is orthodox and half right: manufactured parties burn regime money and collapse when the sexenio changes patrons. The half wrong arrives at the margins — a point of students here, a colonia slate there, the small steady tax that a well-funded imitation levies on the real thing. Affordable opposition is the regime's oldest crop. You have chosen to let this harvest pass.
